Reflection-action run for 2026-07-17 (executed 2026-07-18, unattended).
No commits made this run. Two reasons, both explained below.

STOP CONDITION — uncommitted changes not from this run.
git status at start showed an untracked directory not created by me:
tools/always-on/ (neuroworks-always-on.ps1, stop-always-on.ps1). Per the
hard limits in action-prompt.md, I did not commit, discard, or touch it,
and made no repo changes of my own so its work can't get mixed into an
unattended commit. Investigation below was read-only.

NO ACTIONABLE ITEMS — the reflection has no "What to try next" section.
The 2026-07-17 reflection's entire narrative body is the single line
"An error occurred during input processing. Please try again." — a
provider soft-error string from google/gemini-3.5-flash persisted as if
it were the reflection. Only the frontmatter and raw stats snapshot are
real. Zero bullets to action, so nothing was fixed or flagged from the
reflection content itself.

ROOT CAUSE (read-only, for the operator — this is a real bug worth a fix):
server/src/lib/reflection.ts, synthesizeReflection(), lines ~375-396.
The retry-then-fallback logic only triggers when llmGenerateWithMeta()
THROWS. Here the provider returned HTTP 200 whose generated text was
itself the error message ("An error occurred during input processing.
Please try again." is a known Gemini soft-failure response). Since
nothing threw, the retry never fired, the stat-only fallback (which
would have included a "What to try next" section) never rendered, and
the error string was written to the vault as the day's narrative.
Worse, reflection:daily was recorded ok:1 in the stats — a silent
failure counted as success. Suggested fix when the tree is clean: after
the LLM call, sanity-check meta.text (e.g. reject responses under some
length or matching known provider soft-error phrases) and treat a
failed check like a thrown error so the existing retry + fallback path
handles it. Re-run /api/reflection/run for 2026-07-17 after fixing if
the narrative for that day matters.

BASELINE NOTE: tsc/vitest were not run since no changes were made.
Stats for the day were healthy: 4/4 tasks succeeded, 0 retries,
0 continuations, no failing tools.

PREVIOUS RUNS: the 2026-07-16 and 2026-07-17 raw logs both contain only
"API Error: Unable to connect to API (ConnectionRefused)" — the two
prior scheduled runs of this loop died before doing anything. This is
the first run to complete since 2026-07-11.
